        • [ - ] Zoltan - member since 15-Feb-20

          @Marbella Actually, if you do have an understanding of football, you should know that Bernardo Silva's slow pace and ball possession driven style is a dream for a team such as Sheffield, which likes to park the bus. Phil Foden would have been the correct selection since he is more agile, more unpredictable, and more direct to the goal. This is especially true as Ryad Mahrez, who dominated the previous game with his 3 goals and who represents a similar style, is gone. City's clueless approach to the game visibly had its mental effects on Haaland as well, as the lack of putting pressure on the ball resulted in lack of turnovers and lack of service from his prospective: thus, he missed the penalty. Football is an interesting mental game behind the curtains, and most coaches don't have a proper understanding on how to play this subliminal game that is not visible at all.
